ry described as seeking to stretch “the bond between language and communication.” Calling witness to the narratives of history while pivoting their reach forward to the present, the rhythms, allusions, and resulting outcomes of Carson’s use of language expand both narrative and discovery. movingparts is brought full circle when an unexpected historical connection between Sappho and Aesop is revealed, hinting that what is true or false in the past or present of our lives can arrive at an intimacy with and illumination of more than we imagine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian poetryy20th century. 0aCanadian poetry-20th century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aAesop.  aHesiod.  achange.  acorrect.  acounterparts.  acrow.  adeceit.  adeception.  afable.  afabrication.  afalse.  afalsehood.  afox.  amissing.  amotion.  amyth.  apoetic.  apoetry.  aprimary.  aright.  astory.  atale.  atrue.  atruth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228017493?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228017493423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228017493/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles